review_blob: Overall not bad. Lots of carbonation. Very sweet and syrupy. Tequila Aroma. Slightly dry finish.
Great balance of the described sweet and bitter. Aroma is citrus and floral, preps your palate for an ipa like punch. Flavor is surprisingly sweet and creamy. Very smooth and sessionable.
Nice aroma with a quickly dissipating head. Did a good job of cooling some habenero cheese. Crisp and clean
Super thick n creamy head. Fresh pressed coffee aroma emits from the the pitch black body. Smooth silky coffee notes, roasted malts hit the back end. Good carbonation for a stout.
Golden yellow straw color. Complex hop aroma. Seems like many different hops were used. Body is light and bubbly. Very clean Pale ale.
Amazing Cranberry aroma. Smells like a good Christmas candle. Little head on a dark red body. Cranberry flavor up front with dry cereal. Great season brew!
Malted aroma. Nice white head with a clear red body. Nice lacing down the whole glass. Good balance of malts and hops for a red. A little bit of a dry finish.

No head or carbonation. Black with some red when held to the light. Not much aroma. Raspberry extract flavor. Kind of a bland base beer. No peanut butter flavor detected. 
Was disappointed in this one.
beer_name: Spiteful God Damn Peanut Butter and Jelly Pigeon Porter

review_blob: Creamy chocolate mouthfeel. Oak aftertaste sweet malt but not too heavy. Vanilla and bourbon aroma.
Light cinnamon a aroma. Very dark brown color almost like a stout. Lots of sweet pumpkin flavor. One of the better pumpkin beers.
beer_name: Samuel Adams Fat Jack Double Pumpkin

review_blob: Light yellow straw color, no head. Grassy aroma. Very light flavored and bodied. An ok pilsner style beer.

Poured on tap Nitro. Beautifully cascading brown Nitro carbonation. Thick creamy pure white head. Chocolate aroma. Big chocolate flavor. The Nitro makes it creamy. Heavy full feeling. Lots of chocolate with some roasted aftertaste.
Dark dark brown with thick head and nice lacing. Yeast and banana aroma. A bit hoppy. Fully thick bodied. High carbonation burns the mouth a little
Hop bomb! Citrus pine fruit bouquet of aroma. Served in a goblet, feel like Im drinking a tropical drink. Huge punch of bitterness at first sip. Full bodied with a fruity aftertaste
Poured red amber with small head. Pine aroma. Sweet bitterness. Honey flavor. Dry resin finish. Ok aftertaste
First spicy beer Ive had. Nice to sample but cant imagine drinking a whole glass. The jalapeo gives a great kick!

Wow surprised by this one. Not much peaches flavor but not disappointed!there was subtle peach aroma sitting atop a super light Belgian. How its 10 percent abv and goes down to easily is an art in brewing.
Beautiful red raspberry color matched by a great aroma. Pretty sweet but not to much. Can sense some grains behind the upfront fresh fruit slam.

Citrus hop aroma. Some faint peppery notes underneath. Light yellow like a typical ipa. Bam! Big ipa spice hits the lips and burns the back of the through to. Fun to try but cant drink much (and I love spicy stuff).
Nice citrus and floral hop aroma. Lots of bright white head. Resiny, spruce flavor. Light body.
Clear brown no head. Spicy yeast aroma. Smooth mouthfeel with Complex malts. Sweet finish
Black tan chocolate lookin head choloate Caramel aroma. Tastes like a vanilla coffee. Slight wood and bitterness.

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: Orange amber color with quickly disapating head. Strong nutmeg smell. Taste is also heavily nutmeg spiced. Light carbonation and light body. Clean and tasty beer, just nothing different
beer_name: Magic Hat Wilhelm Scream Pumpkin Ale

review_blob: Black pour, tan head. Chocolate and bread aroma very thick head which retains for awhile. Chocolate hits first. Roasted malts follow. Some lighter Caramel notes detected. Perfect mouth feel for the style
Thick head. Brown in color. Spiced pumpkin aroma. Very pleasant pumpkin flavor. It does taste like pumpkin pie!
Poured into a mug. Great citrus and fruit aroma. Very dark red. Smooth Caramel malty flavor with hops in the background. Moderately bitter.
Medium golden color with lots of carbonation. Beautifully topped with white head. Clean hoppy aroma. Crisp fall taste. Some appley aftertaste lingers.
Overwhelming berry cereal aroma. Smells like after cereal milk. Very sweet and fruity.
Super strong grapefruit aroma upon opening. Pouring brings out even more grapefruit and citrus. Slick and smooth mouthfeel. Very drinkable for the alcohol content.
Perfect 2 finger pour. Black in color. Super strong coffee aroma. Tastes like drinking coffee (black), which I Iike! Very thick and smooth. High alcohol without the bite.
From bottle. Nice pumpkin and cinnamon aroma. Well balance of cinnamon, spices, and roasted pumpkin. Scottish ale backbone rounds it off
Nice wheat and yeast aroma, coriander maybe. Very blue moon like. Belgian yeast maybe gives it that flavor. Simple, no complexity, but thats the style.
Beautiful Thick red head. Vibrant red body in a tulip. Excellent (cascade?) hop aroma. Fresh. Founders never misses!
beer_name: Founders Backstage Series #13: reDANKulous Imperial Red IPA

review_blob: Nutty aroma. Thin and quickly disapating head. Flavor is roasted Caramel. Brown ale reminisce. Light color and body though.
Nice ruby red hue in a tall snifter. 1 finger of white head. Caramel aroma. Dont detect the maple, has body and flavor of an Irish red.
Pours yellow, no head and no carbonation. Metallic and straw flavor. Tastes like a bad bottle but the whole box is the same.
Straw aroma. Yellow straw color with medium carbonation. Very little head. Light almost pilsner like style. Good for hot weather.
Straw Yellow with little head and hardly any carbonation. Grassy aroma. Very light bodied. Creamy and easy to drunk. Good lawnmower beer
Light red /pink with 2 fingers of rapidly disapating head. Sweet cherry wheat aroma. Very light body and overall flavor. Hard to detect and pin anything. Some cherry maybe. Lots of carbonation.
Poured dark amber with nice fluffy white head. Complex malt aroma. Caramel. Sweet maltiness, complex flavor also. Medium carbonation, with very little hops. Nicely balanced esb.
Pours dark brown. Malted chocolate aroma. Sweet maltiness fills the mouth. Carbonation is spot on. Perfect
2 year old bottle. Sour raspberry smell. Tart raspberry taste. Light and fruity. Some vinegar flavor.
Pine and citrus aroma. Medium head with yellow orange hue. Grapefruit and citrus flavor with piney aftertaste. Light body.

Poured into a pint. Copper apple juice like color. Same aroma, fresh pressed apples. Perfect apple flavor. Not too much like a beer and not too much like and overly sweet cider. Low carbonation fits the bill.
beer_name: New Glarus Thumbprint Series Apple Ale

review_blob: Amazing plum aroma,thick white head. Super sweet almost candy Like raisin flavor. No carbonation. Tastes like a fine wine almost.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Drank from can. Sweet grapefruit aroma. Light and a lot of carbonation. Tastes like a radler. A good summer brew. Simple and crisp
Little head with a yellow body. Decent aroma. Fresh hop. Upfront bitter bite. Clean and light.
Bottle to pint with a lime. Better than expected. Light and pretty watery. Hardly any malts and absolutely no hop profile.
Very dark brown. Chocolate and rye aroma. Thick and full bodied. Creamy finish. Sweet overall flavor.
Clear straw yellow pour. Skunky aroma. Dry pils flavor with dry finish. Would not classify this as a wit beer. Pretty standard brew, nothing to write home about.
